<p class='Text' style='font-size: 14px;'>
 <br />We apply the endomorphism&nbsp;&nbsp;<span><math xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML'
    mathematica:form='TraditionalForm'
    xmlns:mathematica='http://www.wolfram.com/XML/'>
 <msub>
  <mi>g</mi>
  <mn>85</mn>
 </msub>
</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;(resp. <span><math xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML'
    mathematica:form='TraditionalForm'
    xmlns:mathematica='http://www.wolfram.com/XML/'>
 <msub>
  <mi>g</mi>
  <mn>98</mn>
 </msub>
</math></span>)&nbsp;&nbsp;over four letters&nbsp;&nbsp;{ <span style='font-style: italic;'>a</span>,<span style='font-style: italic;'>b</span>,<span style='font-style: italic;'>c</span>,<span style='font-style: italic;'>d</span> }&nbsp;&nbsp;to&nbsp;&nbsp;<span><math xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML'
    mathematica:form='TraditionalForm'
    xmlns:mathematica='http://www.wolfram.com/XML/'>
 <msub>
  <mi>g</mi>
  <mn>85</mn>
 </msub>
</math></span>(<span style='font-style: italic;'>a</span>)&nbsp;&nbsp;(resp. <span><math xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML'
    mathematica:form='TraditionalForm'
    xmlns:mathematica='http://www.wolfram.com/XML/'>
 <msub>
  <mi>g</mi>
  <mn>98</mn>
 </msub>
</math></span>(<span style='font-style: italic;'>a</span>)),&nbsp;&nbsp;where&nbsp;&nbsp;<span><math xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML'
    mathematica:form='TraditionalForm'
    xmlns:mathematica='http://www.wolfram.com/XML/'>
 <msub>
  <mi>g</mi>
  <mn>85</mn>
 </msub>
</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;and&nbsp;&nbsp;<span><math xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML'
    mathematica:form='TraditionalForm'
    xmlns:mathematica='http://www.wolfram.com/XML/'>
 <msub>
  <mi>g</mi>
  <mn>98</mn>
 </msub>
</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;are defined (in <span style='font-style: italic;'>Mathematica</span>) as follows: 
</p>



